# ─── Pricing Mentor AI Configuration ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Configure one or more AI providers. The system tries them in order:
# 0. Vercel Proxy (production) – uses server-side DEEPSEEK_KEY
# 1. DeepSeek (direct, for local dev)
# 2. OpenAI (secondary)
# 3. Groq (tertiary)
# 4. Google Gemini (quaternary)
# 5. Local knowledge base (always available as final fallback)

# ─── Server-side (Vercel) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set this in Vercel Environment Variables (Settings > Environment Variables).
# The /api/chat proxy uses this key server-side so it's never exposed to the browser.
# DEEPSEEK_KEY=your_deepseek_api_key_here

# ─── Client-side (local development only) ────────────────────────────────────
# These VITE_* keys are used for local development when the Vercel proxy is
# not available. They are embedded in the frontend bundle — use only in dev.

# DeepSeek API (primary – recommended)
# Get your key at: https://platform.deepseek.com/
VITE_DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=

# OpenAI API (optional fallback)
# Get your key at: https://platform.openai.com/
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Groq API (optional fallback – fast inference for open-source models)
# Get your key at: https://console.groq.com/
VITE_GROQ_API_KEY=

# Google Gemini API (optional fallback)
# Get your key at: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=
